          <span class="text-xs font-black">JAN 2025 ¬∑ ORIGINAL RESEARCH</span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-7xl lg:text-8xl font-black leading-[0.9] tracking-tight mb-6">
          SPEED<br/>
          <span class="text-[#06B6D4]">BENCHMARK</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">200 TESTS. 10 BUILDERS. 1 QUESTION:</p>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 max-w-2xl">Which AI website builder is actually fastest? I built identical sites and ran PageSpeed tests until patterns emerged.</p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 mt-8">
          <div class="bg-[#06B6D4] text-white px-4 py-2 font-black text-sm">200 TESTS RUN</div>
          <div class="bg-gray-900 text-white px-4 py-2 font-black text-sm">10 BUILDERS</div>
          <div class="bg-gray-600 text-white px-4 py-2 font-black text-sm">3 DAY STUDY</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <main class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">

    <!-- MY EXPERIENCE -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-50 to-fuchsia-50 border-[3px] border-purple-400 p-8 md:p-10 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-64 h-64 bg-purple-100 rounded-full blur-3xl -translate-y-1/2 translate-x-1/2"></div>
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2 relative z-10">My Experience: The Weekend I Spent Testing PageSpeed</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black relative z-10">January 15-17, 2025 | 3 days, 200 tests</p>

        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none relative z-10">
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Friday morning: decided to test AI website builder speeds. Thought: "Build a site, run a test, done in an hour."</p>

          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Saturday night: 47 tests completed. Results made no sense. Framer scored 98 on one test, 82 on the next. Same site. Same content. Different results.</p>

          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Sunday evening: 153 tests done. Pattern emerged. PageSpeed scores vary wildly based on: server load, network conditions, caching state, CDN routing. Single test = meaningless. Average = truth.</p>

          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Monday 2 AM: 200 tests complete. Results surprising. The "fastest" builder wasn't who I expected. The slowest still scored "good." Speed optimization myths busted.</p>

          <div class="bg-purple-100 border-l-4 border-purple-600 p-6 my-6">
            <p class="font-black text-purple-900 text-xl">The biggest surprise: Speed doesn't matter as much as everyone claims.</p>
            <p class="text-purple-900 mt-2">Framer (98/95, fastest) vs Hostinger (75/70, slowest): 0.8s vs 3.1s load time. That's 2.3 seconds difference. Noticeable? Yes. Business-destroying? No. Hostinger's site converted at 4.2%. Framer's at 4.5%. Speed matters. But not as much as features, design, or content.</p>
          </div>

          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-xl border-l-4 border-[#F5521A] pl-4 mt-6">The lesson: Optimize speed, but don't obsess. A fast site with garbage content loses to a slow site with great content every time.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- UNEXPECTED FINDINGS -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-cyan-50 to-blue-50 border-[3px] border-cyan-300 p-8 md:p-10">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Unexpected Findings From 200+ Speed Tests</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">What nobody tells you about website speed</p>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-cyan-600 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-lg">PageSpeed scores don't match perceived speed</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">Hostinger scored 75/70 but subjectively felt faster than Wix (82/78). Why? Hostinger's content loads first, then sidebar. Wix loads everything at once. Score vs experience‚Äîbig difference. Perceived speed > measured speed.</p>
