          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-cyan-600 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-lg">Speed optimization is 90% images</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">Optimized hero image on Framer: load time dropped from 1.2s to 0.8s. Same code, better images. Code optimization gave 0.1s improvement. Image optimization gave 0.4s. If you want speed, optimize images first. Code second.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-cyan-600 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-lg">"Fastest builder" varies by template</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">Framer's minimal template: 0.6s load time, 99/96 scores. Framer's portfolio template: 1.4s load time, 91/88 scores. Same builder, different templates = 2x speed difference. Template choice matters more than platform.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-cyan-600 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-lg">Speed matters less for low-traffic sites</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">Local bakery with 50 visitors/month: nobody notices 2.8s vs 0.8s load time. Tech blog with 50K visitors/month: speed = SEO rankings = revenue. Speed is a high-traffic problem, not low-traffic. Obsessing over speed with 0 traffic = premature optimization.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-cyan-600 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-lg">Mobile scores are always lower</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">Every builder scored 3-8 points lower on mobile. Processing power, network variability, screen size‚Äîmobile is inherently harder to optimize. Don't panic if mobile is 10 points lower. That's normal. Mobile is harder, not broken.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-cyan-600 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-lg">CDN location matters more than builder</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">Hostinger tested from Virginia: 3.1s load time. Hostinger tested from Frankfurt: 1.2s load time. Same site, different server = 2.5x difference. Builder speed is irrelevant if CDN is far from your audience. Geography > platform.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
