    </section>

    <!-- BRUTAL TRUTH -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-900 to-black text-white border-[3px] border-[#06B6D4] p-8 md:p-10">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-2">The Brutal Truth: Speed is Overrated</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">Reality check</p>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-200">Speed matters. But not as much as the SEO industry claims.</p>

          <p class="text-lg text-gray-200">Google says: "Sites should load in 2.5 seconds or less."</p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-200">Reality: Sites loading in 4 seconds outrank 1-second sites constantly. Why? Because speed is ONE of 200+ ranking factors. Content quality, backlinks, relevance, user intent‚Äîall matter more.</p>

