          <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 mt-4">
            <li>‚Ä¢ User searches for "plumber Chicago"</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Google returns results based on RELEVANCE first, speed second</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ User clicks result #1 (loads in 2.8s)</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ User finds answer, leaves satisfied</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Google notes: good user experience, keep ranking</li>
          </ul>

          <p class="text-lg text-gray-200 mt-6">Speed becomes a problem at 5+ seconds. Under 3 seconds? You're fine. Under 2 seconds? Diminishing returns. Optimizing from 2s to 0.8s won't move rankings. Content will.</p>

